          <h2>Symptoms of Stress in a Student</h2>

          <p>Stress with negative short-term effects will arise, both for the student and the OJTI.</p>

          <p>The <strong>symptoms</strong> are most noticeable when the person is in stress overload. However, remember that many students, for several reasons, are able to hide their symptoms through various  strategies. This may lead you to think that there is no problem, or make it difficult to realise that there is a problem. This may make the <strong>recognition</strong> of stress symptoms in others <strong>very difficult</strong>.</p>

          {# <p class="oj-dev-notes">tabs</p> #}

          <p>In general, responses to stress overload fall into one of four categories:</p>

        </div>

        <div class="ians-column-wide-5">

