                  <li>Procrastinating or neglecting responsibilities</li>
                  <li>Eating more or less</li>
                  <li>Sleeping too much or too little</li>
                  <li>Isolating yourself from others</li>
                  <li>Abuse of alcohol, cigarettes or drugs to relax</li>
                  <li>Nervous habits</li>
                  <li>Explosiveness</li>
                </ul>

                <div class="ians-bg-blue-dark oj-list-symptoms-text oj-notched">
                  <p>Stress overload can affect the way a student acts at work, at home and/or with friends. At times, stress may become so severe that <strong>alcohol</strong> is used to self-medicate anxiety or depression.</p>

                  <p>Using alcohol as a coping strategy is particularly dangerous since it impairs judgement and increases impulsivity. </p>

                  {% image "images/behavioural.jpg", "A sad looking man sitting at a table drinking alcohol."%}
