            <div class="oj-notched">
              <h3>
                <span>1</span> Self-confidence</h3>
              <p>They should have a high, but realistic degree of <strong>self-confidence</strong> in their learning ability. To feel unsure, generates negative thoughts that interfere with training. From an instructor perspective, you can <strong>reduce</strong> feelings of <strong>uncertainty</strong> by being <strong>clear about the training objectives and unambiguous in your debriefing</strong> with the student about their performance.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="oj-notched">
              <h3>
                <span>2</span> Positive learning environment</h3>
              <p>They should feel that they are in a <strong>positive learning environment</strong> where success is acknowledged, and they know they will get predictable and reliable support from their instructor.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="oj-notched">
              <h3>
                <span>3</span> Clear training process</h3>
              <p>They should have a clear understanding of the <strong>training process</strong> they are going through and what is <strong>expected</strong> from them. A comprehensive UTP and clear training objectives for each session is necessary for this condition to be met.</p>
